               <p>A native of <placeName>Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire</placeName>, Bardsley was
                  admitted as a <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> in <date when="1768"
                     >1768</date> (<hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 10:353). He continued to serve long
                  past <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>John Wesley</persName>&apos;s
                  death, and was one of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                     />Wesley</persName>&apos;s favorites. See <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 58; <hi
                     rend="italic">MM</hi> 41 (<date when="1818">1818</date>): 348; <hi
                     rend="italic">Minutes</hi> (post-Wesley, <date when="1819">1819</date>), 5:5–6;
                  and Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 19.</p>
